Lawrence Selden is Selden is a detached observer of the New York society that Lily aspires to join. He is a lawyer by profession, but he is not particularly wealthy, which prevents Lily from marrying him even though they love one another. Throughout the novel, Selden struggles between his desire to remain detached from society and his wish to court Lily and convince her to marry him. At the end of the novel, he resolves finally to propose marriage to Lily, but his decision comes too lateâ€”he finds her dead in her apartment.